    "guidance": "Pipelines are composable, reusable AI processing chains. They separate the WHAT (your prompt template) from the HOW (which model, which transforms).\n\nA pipeline is built by chaining:\n• aiMessage() — the prompt template with ${variable} placeholders\n• .to(aiModel()) — connect to a model\n• .transform() — post-process the output\n\nThe ${variable} placeholder syntax lets you create reusable templates:\n    pipeline = aiMessage().user(\"Translate '${text}' to ${language}\").toDefaultModel()\n    result1 = pipeline.run({ text: \"Hello\", language: \"Spanish\" })\n    result2 = pipeline.run({ text: \"Hello\", language: \"French\" })\n\nThe special ${_input} variable holds the output of the previous pipeline step, enabling multi-stage chains.\n\nPipelines are especially useful when you want to: process lists of items with the same prompt, A/B test prompts, or build reusable AI utilities in your service layer.",
    "output": "=== Translation Pipeline ===\nSpanish : ¡Hola! Estoy aprendiendo BoxLang y es increíble.\nFrench  : Bonjour ! J'apprends BoxLang et c'est incroyable.\nGerman  : Hallo! Ich lerne BoxLang und es ist unglaublich.\n\n=== Word count from transform ===\nWord count: 9",
